animal.description:
NOTE: DELLA needs to be the only dog in the home, no cats either. She also needs a fenced yard.

DELLA's first few months of life were wretched---she lived in a filthy crate in a backyard until she was confiscated from her "owner" by cruelty investigators. At the time she was rescued, DELLA was about nine months old and weighed only 17 pounds--she was literally skin and bones --her fur was scanty, her ribs and hipbones were fully visible, and her paws were splayed from malnutrition. DELLA is now a normal weigh for her size, and enjoys the activities she had been deprived of in her former life. Her coat is thicker and more lustrous and she now has the stamina to play and run in her fenced yard. Despite the neglect she experienced, DELLA is a happy girl and she is looking for a forever home with guardians who will provide security, care and love.

This pet is spayed or neutered in accordance with our strict policy wherein all animals are altered prior to adoption. This pet is dewormed, current on vaccines, and started on monthly flea/tick and preventatives. Animal Alliance's policy is that we will adopt dogs younger than 1 year old to families with children under 9 years old. We do not adopt dogs 1 year or older to families with children under 9 years old due to the unknown history of adult dogs. Prior to submitting an application, please see the Animal Alliance Adoption Process for adoption details. WE DO NOT HAVE OPEN HOURS! WE MEET ADOPTERS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY!!!! AN ONLINE APPLICATION IS THE FIRST STEP TO MEETING A NEW PET. Once your application is approved, our adoption coordinator will be in touch with you to set up a meeting. Some animals are in our adoption center; others are in foster homes. PLEASE DO NOT COME TO OUR ADOPTION CENTER UNLESS YOU HAVE AN APPROVED APPLICATION AND AN APPOINTMENT. To fill out an adoption application, go to: https://www.animalalliancenj.org/fosteradoption-application/

animal.description:
Hi I'm Luke! I am sweet, loyal and loving to all humans. I love belly rubs, walks, and naps with my foster dad. I'm a 6-7 year old special needs dog. I had a very tough time before DFW Tzu's took me in. My right eye was badly damaged and had to be removed but I am sighted in my left eye and can get around just fine. I can see darkness and light and shadows. I have no problems getting around but I have to have over the counter Systane to keep my left eye moist so I can continue to see. Also I have to take medication twice a day to prevent very mild seizures. Nothing dramatic. My foster dad can fill you in if you want to meet me and I hope you do! I prefer to be an alone dog but get along well with a calm female companion pup. I need someone at home most of the day but I'm ok if your gone for a few hours. I'm well house trained and if you let me outside regularly I won't make mistakes. I'm also trained on potty pads! I can't be baby gated in a room alone or crated, I panic. If house loose I won't make a mess, chew or damage anything. I just like to be a couch potato and will sleep a lot. I am curious about children but really don't like to be around them. I get scared. If you have had dogs with sight issues and want a funny handsome new family member I could be the one! All DFW Tzus dogs are spayed/neutered, UTD on vaccines, heart worm tested and on heart worm preventative and microchipped. Please go to our website: www.dfwtzusandmorerescue.com for complete instructions on our adoption process and for adoption application. Check our website for directions/times of our next Tzu Review/Adoption event at a local Petsmart. Note: The children of adopters must be age 6 or older. WE ADOPT IN THE DFW METROPLEX AREA ONLY.

WE ARE ALWAYS IN NEED OF VOLUNTEERS/FOSTER HOMES.


 PLEASE GO TO OUR WEBSITE TO COMPLETE A VOLUNTEER/FOSTER APPLICATION OR TO MAKE A DONATION TO ASSIST WITH THE MEDICAL CARE OF OUR RESCUED DOGS. We are a 501c3. We rely on your generosity and donations in order to cover the medical costs of our many needy dogs Your donations are tax deductible!

animal.description:
Sonny is an 11 year old (as of April 2019) Chinese Crested/Chihuahua mixed dog.  He was surrendered to the Humane Society because his mom developed medical conditions that didn't allow her to be able to care for him.  

He is a very laid back, chill dog.  He is good with other dogs as long as they aren't too rambunctious.  He prefers to sit with his human and be petted than to play.  He will run and play a little in the yard, but once he's inside, play time is over.  If you're looking for a true lap dog, your search is over.

Sometimes, it seems like he knows exactly what you're saying to him.  He's reactive to being given directions.  He does have a mind of his own, though.  He knows the command "Get in your crate" but doesn't like it, so he will jump on the sofa instead.  lol  Then I will carry him to his crate.

He is not house trained or crate trained.  Being a small dog, he does have accidents in his crate overnight and during the day when he's left for an extended period of time.  He does mark, so a belly band is being used.

If you are interested in adopting this particular dog or puppy, please see our Adoption Guidelines at http://www.humanesocietyall.com/applications.  If you feel like you qualify for adoption, please fill out our Dog Adoption Application which can be found at the same link. Be sure to save your completed application before closing it so you will not lose your information. You may return the completed application via email to  jessica_adams147@yahoo.com. Please allow 1-3 business days for your application to be reviewed. Thank you for considering adoption of a rescued pet!

Even if you are unable to adopt one of our pets at this time, please consider sponsoring this pet with a donation. No donation is ever too small and allows us to keep saving lives.  Our paypal address is:  paypal@humanesocietyall.com

Thank you!

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullBreed: Pit Bull Terrier Gender: Female Estimated Date of Birth: August 3, 2010 Size: 51 lbs Location: Brookhaven, GA
RESCUING MIA
Mia is the epitome of Forlorn. This poor lady was dumped at a church in rural Paulding County with nasty ear infections, worn down teeth, terribly itchy skin, and painful tumors. We were able to fix Mia up and remove her tumors. Her large tumor that was dragging on the ground ended up being a giant benign skin-tag! Despite being in such rough shape, she was always happy and loves attention.
ABOUT MIA
Mia is enjoying the pampered life of being a loved house-dog. She seems to be a bit dominant with other dogs at first, but she definitely wants to play. Her foster-mom took introductions slow and she is now best friends with her doggie foster siblings. Mia is very in-tune with any noise from the kitchen and will be there within seconds upon first wrapper tare. She loves to squeeze her big self between you and the couch as she loves attention, but is not overly demanding about it. Overall, Mia is very low key. She is has learned many manners like how to sit, wait for her meals, walk on a leash, and come when she's called. When treats are involved, this lady is a quick learner! Mia has been fully vetted. Mia is a happy, very sweet little lady who is looking for a family of her very own!
Photo Album of Mia: https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.2018337798224376&type=1&l=27ac60d10b
Our adoption fee is $300. All dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, on heartworm prevention, and are fed top of the line grain-free food.www.savingpitbulls.org

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Personality:

None of our foster dogs are tested with cats and we have no way of testing them with cats. Siberians are notorious for their high prey drive and typically kill cats, rabbits, chickens, birds, squirrels, opossums, etc., so we we don't have much success adopting them out to homes with cats. Most of our foster dogs are with us for killing cats, chickens and goats to begin with so our assumption is they are not good with cats and other small things that move.

Siberians are typically good with children of all ages and the only reason we would not list them as not good with kids is because they may be too energetic and bouncy and knock over a toddler.

Southern Siberian Rescue is a volunteer based 501(c)3 organization based out of Raleigh, NC, so we do not have a physical facility with operating hours that you can visit to meet our dogs. All of our foster dogs are in our personal homes. You need to fill out our adoption application (http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption) and get approved to adopt and then we will set a time for you to meet our foster dogs. As a volunteer based group, we all have jobs, family, personal dogs and other commitments but we try to acknowledge and process applications as quickly as we can. That being said, we try to keep our available foster dogs as current as we can also but it is time consuming to get pics and information on new dogs so not all of our dogs are listed at all times. Please fill out our application and then we can discuss dogs that will work for you and your situation. We average 40-45 Siberians in our program so we are certain we have one that will work for you. Please know that we are not obligated to answer inquiries on dogs as we will focus on approved applicants. Again, there is ample time to discuss all of our foster dogs AFTER we have an approved application on file. We do adopt out of state as long as we can get a home check done. We ask that you, your family and existing pets make the trip to NC to meet and adopt our foster dogs.

SSR can not and will not hold dogs for anyone. If we do, that means another Siberian will die in a shelter because a shelter dogs time is very limited, as is our foster space. We do our best to process applications in the order received and first application gets first interest in our foster dog(s). We understand that there will be scheduling conflicts with home checks and meet and greets but we will try to accommodate for that if a potential adopter has interest in a particular foster dog in our program.

All Southern Siberian Rescue foster dogs are microchipped, up to date on shots, spay/neutered, on monthly heartworm preventative and flea and tick preventative. For additional information on Southern Siberian Rescue and Siberian Huskies, please visit www.SouthernSiberian.com. To fill out an application, please visit

http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption
.

animal.description:
Zelda bean is a very exuberant two-year-old. She has a zest for life and she has not meet a person that she doesn’t seem to love! She enjoys having a job and can spend hours playing nose work and scent games. Zelda has attended training classes to work on her basic manners, more polite greetings and classes to keep that sharp mind engaged. Zelda would do best in an extremely active home environment. A home that has time to both physically and mentally exercise her daily. Zelda can be too excitable with other dogs; it is this behavior that has limited her canine friends. Her ideal placement will be a single dog home. This exuberance level also has us looking for a home with no small children, as they can be easily knocked down. 

Our adoption process starts with our application. Once the application is approved, a member of Legacy will contact you to set up a home visit. The home visit usually last 1- 1 1/2 hours and is to make sure our dog and any current dogs/cats are getting along, as well as both of us agreeing it's a fit. At this time the adoption fee is due, and begins the 2 week trial. We will check in during the 2 week trial. If it's not working, our dog is returned to the foster home and all except $100.00 of the adoption fee is returned. At the end of the 2 week trial, you decide if you will finalize the adoption - if finalized, the Adoption Contract is signed and all medical records are turned over to you. If at any time you need to rehome the dog it contractually needs to be returned to Legacy Dog Rescue.

ADOPTION FEE's:
Puppies under 6 months:  $199.00
Adults:  $150.00
Seniors (over 7 yrs):  $99.00

If you are interested in one of our dogs please fill out an application: 
https://form.jotform.com/193425528783165

animal.description:
Bubbles has an enlarged heart
Although we do our very best to make sure your new pup is in tiptop health before adoption, things could drastically change a month later. Since we don't have a long health history of your adopted dog, we can only treat her for whatever symptoms that present during the initial exam and follow up exams. - -

Health: When Bubbles first came into our rescue (early 2018) a benign mass was removed from her neck. She also was successfully treated for heart worms and numerous parasites. This girl was very sick when we first received her.

*****On April 24th, she was diagnosed with an enlarged heart. She is on Lasix and Enalapril twice a day for the rest of her life. Initially it was difficult to administer her medication. She now enjoys her medication when it is put into a small bit of liverwurst and offered as a "treat". ***** No other obvious health issues have been diagnosed. - -

Temperament: She has only been used for breeding, so she is more comfortable being with dogs than people. It will take some time and patience for her to learn that people can be nice. If you decide to adopt Bubbles, I hope you will consider that
it will take some time
before she becomes the lap dog you might be hoping for. Bubbles has been seriously mistreated her whole life. She is not going to trust you immediately. Please don't apply to adopt her unless you are very serious about putting in the time it will take to help her adjust to a "normal" dog life. -----------------------------------------------------------

She has never bitten anyone but she does run from you when she is outside and she will back herself into a corner when you reach for her inside. When you reach down to pick her up, she will throw her front paws up in the air and it almost looks like a small child reacting to someone picking them up. It would be funny except that she does it out of fear. I believe
it will take a very long time for bubbles to relax and enjoy being part of the family.
She will not be easy but it will be very rewarding when she comes to you for a treat and to enjoy some ear scratching for the first time. Update 7/1/2019 Bubbles still retreats if you go to get her; however, she is starting to come and laydown and relax near her foster family daily especially if another dog is already there. She likes to be on the sofa and bed and will use dog steps to get up and down from the bed. --------------------------

Bubbles knows how to use a doggie door. She is crate trained as well. She is walking very well on a leash hooked to her collar or harness. She likes the harness the best and it's the safest way to walk her. She is most cooperative when walking alongside other confident dogs but she will walk by herself too. She will just be more on alert.

Where did she come from: She came from puppy mill closure. It was a really awful place. --

Adoption: $324.75 ($300.00 fee + $24.75 required 8.25% sales tax)
Weight: 9 lbs.
DOB: 2/8/2009

ADOPTION APPLICATION: http://www.recycledpoms.org/application

Email info@recycledpomeranians.com to request a printable application.

------Please remember our group is made of only volunteers all of whom have full time jobs, foster fur-kids, and families of their own, so please be patient.--------- 2/2/21 3:35 PM

animal.description:
SWEET, SWEET BUTCH!!  Butch's story is just one of many heartbreakers.  We only know a part of what has happened in his life.  We know he was taken from his mom and siblings too soon and we know he was tied up with a wire or coat hanger at some point.  The scar around his neck has healed but I'm sure the trauma remains.  Then he was left in Houston in a backyard to drown during Hurricane Harvey.  He was rescued by a group of dedicated volunteers who were in boats searching for dogs in danger. Butch was heartworm positive, too, but has now been treated and is very healthy.  

Luckily for Butch, his rescuer was very committed and dedicated to him.  Butch spent two months with a behaviorist with fabulous results and has made dramatic improvements.  He has learned to be a happy dog, But some things remain and will always be with him.  

Butch needs a quiet, structured home with adults only.  No other animals, no children.  No exceptions.  This is not because he is aggressive -- far from it.  Butch is extremely affectionate and wants to please.  It is because he is fearful of quick movements and too much noise and energy.  Surprisingly, Butch has not shown any storm fearfulness, per se. 

Butch LOVES his toys!!!  He has little bear, big bear and Mr. Hedgehog!  When he comes out of his kennel, he brings each one out, too, to lie down with him.  He has never torn  up his "friends" either. 

Our dream home for Butch would be an "early retired" couple or single person looking for a faithful and loving companion. Butch loves to take walks, but generally prefers to be a homebody and feel secure. 

Please help us find the perfect home for this beautiful, sweet, deserving boy.

animal.description:
I am willing to waive most of her adoption fee down to just $75 this month. I’d love for her to find the perfect home to accept her “special need”. Rosie has epilepsy that is well controlled with phenobarbital. She has not had a seizure in many months. She goes in once a year for bloodwork just to monitor her levels. The last time she had a cluster of seizures was this past summer and the vet increased her dose to better control it. In the past when she has had seizures, we just keep calm and they pass fairly quickly. 
Her medication costs about $40/ month.
Rosie was surrendered to us by her family in 2018. They were dealing with an at risk pregnancy and did not have time for her.  
She would thrive in a home with a fenced yard, no other dogs and someone to love her like she deserves.
Rosie is about 4 years old. She is spayed and up to date on vaccines. She is house trained and good in her crate. She is a well behaved co-pilot in the car. 
Rosie’s personality is very puppy like and she thoroughly enjoys every minute of her life. She easily makes me smile as she is playing with her toys or entertaining herself in the yard, and they way she runs and dances around the yard is a joyful sight. She loves to get the zoomies and stretch her long legs out. She likes to play keep away with her ball, but will chase it for as long as you will throw it.
animal.name: Rosie

animal.description:
OH HAI! Are you this "light at the end of the tunnel" I keep hearing about? Are you my furever home? Are those adoption PAPERS you're signing? And do they say "Savitar" on them? That's MY name! (scrunches eyes tight) Please don't let this be a dream...please don't let this be a dream...



UPDATE 1/10/19  Savatar has made great progress during his time at our rescue. He gets along with the dogs at his foster home and does fine with them however if he doesn't know a dog he is very confrontational and aggressive. For this reason we think he should be an only dog unless he is adopted with Simi who came to us with him and they were surrendered at the kill shelter together.  Savatar does great with the kids in his foster home ages 12-15 yrs but unless constantly supervised we feel he needs to be in a home without kids.  

Savatar takes a long time to build trust. The abuse he suffered was terrible and he needs a home that will understand, be firm and not afraid to help him adjust.  


UPDATE:9/25/18 Savitar is making great strides in his touch therapy. Savitar can now be pet just about anywhere as long as he isn't startled. Savitar is learning to get along with the other members of the pack at the rescue but he still tries to challenge the dominant male. We still recommend only females or he be an only dog. Savitar has gain about 15 lbs since we first pulled him from the kill shelter and is no longer gobbling his food down. He is starting to understand that not all humans are bad and there is more food coming. We recommend an experienced rottie person. 

Savitar was pulled from a kill shelter where he was owner surrendered severely emaciated and showing signs of being abused. Savitar was surrendered with his mate Simi who we also have. 

Savitar has a few issues we are currently working on. He does not like to be touch on both sides of his head/muzzle. He flinches away from unexpected touch but on the other hand he is very affectionate and can often be found trying to crawl in the lap and lay his head on the shoulder of one of the founders.  However, the sensitivity to touch in certain locations we do not recommend young children.

Savitar is fine with all of the dogs in our pack except our pack leader. Savitar tries to challenge him for dominance.  For this reason we suggest he be the only male dog.  

Savitar is really a sweet dog given the chance and just needs to right understanding owner to help him learn to trust people again.  Savitar enjoys his daily runs with one of the founders sons (14yrs old) and can often be found visiting with the bull we have at our rescue.  

Savitar is crate trained, potty trained, working on basic obedience and leash manners and experiencing touch therapy to help him learn that not all touch is bad.

animal.description:
Foster Homes Needed!

Do you have time and room in your life for a foster dog?

http://www.muttloverescue.org/foster.html

*****************

Our girl Abbie- this stunner with the super model looks and brains of a border collie, is still waiting for her perfect family! Abbie is a very special girl who's had a rough time of it so far. Taken from a neglectful situation as a skinny, wormy bellied puppy, she has spent the majority of her young life in boarding (well cared for, but not a home). New situations are difficult for her and she needs routine and patience to help settle her into her new home. While Abbie enjoys playing with some dogs, she chooses her friends carefully and has decided she would rather not share a home with a canine (or feline) pal. We certainly don't blame her, she's waited this long, she deserves the attention all for herself! A home with a securely fenced yard she can run and play in, a quiet neighborhood for daily walks, a comfy crate complete with her favorite nylabone for security, an experienced, active adult family with NO kids, who will give her the routine and time she needs to settle in - these are all on Abbie's wish list for her new family. You will be rewarded with a super snuggly, silly girl to entertain you.. If you fit the bill, she'd love to meet you! Abbie is approximately two years young and weighs a bit under 50 lbs.

**BECAUSE OF OUR REQUIREMENT FOR A HOME VISIT, WE ARE ONLY ABLE TO ADOPT TO HOMES IN THE NORTHERN VA / MARYLAND / DC METRO AREA**

We have adoption events EVERY SATURDAY from 12-3 p.m. Please note that not all dogs can attend every event, so if you are interested in meeting a particular dog, please complete a no-obligation application on our website at http://www.muttloverescue.org/application.html OR write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

Upcoming adoption events:

Mutt Love Rescue is doing everything we can to ensure the health and safety of our volunteers and adopters while continuing our mission to find homes for as many dogs as possible.

Effective immediately, we will not be holding our weekly adoption events. Dogs available for adoption can be met by appointment only. Potential adopters should submit an online application at http://muttloverescue.org/application.html. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to let you know the next steps.

We are always desperate for foster homes, now more than ever. If you are interested in fostering during this difficult time, please complete an application... unless you are a previous adopter/foster, then you can just contact us via phone (703-988-2608) or email (adopt@muttloverescue.org) to tell us which dog you want to foster!

For information on sponsoring this dog, please write to adopt@muttloverescue.org.

WE NEED FOSTER HOMES! FOR MORE INFORMATION, PLEASE EMAIL ADOPT@MUTTLOVERESCUE.ORG.

Visit us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/muttloverescue
Follow us on Twitter: @Muttlove_Rescue

animal.description:
NOTE: Adoptions are by appointment only. If you are seriously interested in adopting an animal that you see on this site, one that is located at the county animal shelter, please call the shelter for information about the animal you are considering and to get information about how adoptions may take place now that the “stay at home” order is lifted, to ensure your safety and the safety of the staff using social distancing protocols now in place. 

BE PATIENT!!!  AND BE KIND TO THE STAFF.  They take excellent care of the animals and facilities with the small, core staff and funds they are allocated through the county budget.  For more information about the county animal shelter policies and procedures, please go to the Cumberland County, Tennessee government website. Click on Departments, then Mayor’s departments, and then click on Animal shelter. Many local residents are not aware that the specific purpose and mission of the animal shelter is limited to taking in and caring for animals brought in by the animal control officers employed by the county and the City of Crossville. It is not required to accept stray animals from the public, nor is it required to accept animals surrendered by the public. Whether they choose to do so now that the “stay at home” policy is lifted, is up to the county and Is subject to change at any time without notice.

NOTE: You actually CAN donate to the shelter directly by making your check out to Cumberland County AND noting on the check: “Animal Shelter Donation.”  Or you can use the donate feature on Petfinder which allows you to donate money to sponsor pets at the shelter. You may not designate the specific animal, or how the money is to be used. However, be assured that the money will be directed to the animal shelter donation fund by the county. Anyone wishing to continue to donate needed goods at this critical time, such as dry or wet dog food, dry or wet cat food, cat litter, paper towels, bleach, sanitizing hand wipes, clean towels is still welcome to do so.   Call first so that they can tell you how you can safely get the donated items into their hands.

This petfinder shelter site is maintained by a private citizen and not the shelter staff. So, PLEASE call them during them during their normal, but limited, business hours if you have questions and to determine if an animal you are considering adopting is still available.  

All stray dogs, cats, puppies and kittens that arrive at the shelter must meet certain city or county hold periods to give owners a chance to find and claim them.  Even animals surrendered by their owners are held by the shelter for sufficient time to evaluate their general health, their reaction to vaccines and dewormers and their suitability for adoption to the public.  

KITTENS and PUPPIES are held for approximately (at least) 16 days from the date of intake so that their first two shots can be administered, two weeks apart.  Even then, if they do not meet spay/neuter weight requirements, it will be even longer before they are available.  Unfortunately, vaccines can, and often do, cause the animals to experience symptoms of the very diseases and conditions they are designed to prevent.  

So, even after they have had the second vaccine, if the symptoms appear, staff has to start a 2-week course of antibiotic treatment with each animal thus infected.  

With the opening of the new adoption center in July 2018, all of the animals are no longer housed in the same building.

The building called the "intake facility" is used to house all incoming animals. It is closed to the general public.  Only those people dropping off stray or surrendered animals and those who are looking for their missing pets will be directed by the adoption center staff to the intake building.  There is no public parking at that building and staff will direct you as to how to walk to that building if they authorize you to do so.

Those who are looking to adopt an animal are asked to go to the new adoption center which is to your left as you come through the gates and up the driveway.  The old building to the right is closed to the public.

If you are interested in an animal whose photo you see online, you must schedule an appointment with staff at the adoption center to see it. You may also check with staff by telephone first to determine if it has been adopted. This is highly recommended, especially if you will be driving quite a distance. If you schedule an adoption appointment to meet with a cat or a dog that is already spayed or neutered, that animal is able to go home the same day that it is adopted. Staff strongly encourages you to bring an appropriate sized cat carrier or dog crate, as well as your own leash, to make sure that you and your new pet arrive home safely together.

Because animals can become ill at any time even after they go to the adoption center, staff may have to return them to the intake facility for further evaluation and treatment.  Their pictures still may be on petfinder.com as available. This is is not done to frustrate you!  This site is maintained by a private citizen to help get general information on shelter animals out to the public looking for lost animals and to adopt new family pets. Staff may make more animals available for adoption at the shelter before they can be added to this site. Likewise, some animals may be removed from adoptable status at any time and those may not be reflected to this site right away. For your best adoption experience, call the shelter staff before you decide to head to their location. Get all of the information concerning the animal’s temperament, Health history while at the shelter, availability, the adoption paperwork and related fees, animal shelter hours and method of payment before driving to their location.

animal.description:
Why hello Boogie!!

Boogie is a stunning female Pit Bull X who is about 5yrs old. She is very sweet and loving with her adult humans and older kids. She is very active and loves to play play play! She can't wait to have her very own fenced yard to run around in. She would be a great buddy to go on long walks with or hiking with. She is just ready to explore the world and all it has to offer. 

Boogie is not a fan of other dogs and likes all of the attention for herself. She needs to be the only dog in the home and is not a dog park candidate. She also has some guarding issues and young children who don't understand and have tiny fingers are not a good fit for her.  However, Boogie is working on some of her issues.

 Her adoption includes the following training:  3 in home sessions (the first being when he is brought to his forever home). 2 six week classes (basic obedience & intermediate obedience) and unlimited play groups for 3 month.

If you look into Boogies eyes and see the love and possibility, then fill out an application to adopt her here: http://www.moemoesrescue.com

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Gus!

I am a 3-year-old Pit Bull mixI'm healthy, vaccinated, and neutered. Please don't be afraid of me because of my breed!

I love humans and I'm great with kids. Unfortunately, I don't do well with other dogs; part of me would love another doggie friend, and maybe with some more training that would be possible, but for now, I need an owner that respects my need to stay away from other pups. Cats are also off-limits because I think it's fun to chase them - they look like chew toys to me

Most importantly I will love my humans with all my heart. I will wait outside of the bathroom to make sure they are ok. I will want to cuddle up with them at night. Anywhere my humans go is where I want to be. I do have some abandonment issues, so please be patient with me. I will get more comfortable and secure over time. Please give me a chance to have a forever home, you won't regret it!

If you would like to meet Gus, please submit a completed
adoption application found
at www.doggiebonez.com so that we can schedule a meet and greet. He is also on all of our social media pages IG: @Doggie_Bonez_Inc_ and Facebook: Doggie Bonez.

If adoption isn't an option, please consider fostering one of our pups. We are a volunteer-run non-profit dog rescue and always welcome new short or long term doggie foster families. animal.description:
Heartland generally serves Indiana, Kentucky and the Cincinnati areas. However we cannot cover every area.  We do work with our sister and brother rescues in other areas as well. Please consider your local Sheltie rescue before applying outside your area. 

We will NOT ship our available dogs.  A home visit by a volunteer is required before an application can be approved.  ********************************************************************************************
Hope is a shy little Sheltie girl.  She loves to play with the other Shelties in her foster home but she is still wary of people.   She will cower when cornered to be picked up.  She has also displayed some submissive wetting though that is not consistent. 

She is a good traveler but she is a HUGE flight risk! A securely fenced yard is required in Hope's forever home.

Hope is a totally different dog when she doesn't know a person is watching,  She runs and plays. But as soon as a person is seen, she's back to shy little Hope.  She will need another confident, playful dog in  her forever home.

She takes treats nicely and loves braunschweiger.  

Hope will be 3 years old in Septemeber. She came from a commercial breeding facility.  She's learning what it's like to be a companion but it will take some time.  Hope will require completion of a basic, group obedience class as part of her adoption agreement.  We feel that will help improve her self esteem and make her a more confident dog.  Enrollment must be done within 30 days of placement and proof of completion provided within 120 days of placement.    

Hope has a thick, plush coat!  She is easy to groom but be prepared for lots of brushing!

Hope is not good with smaller or more submissive dogs.  She wants to be in charge. 

Apply to adopt Hope at www.SheltieRescue.org
Hope's adoption fee is $450

animal.description:
Hope and her siblings were part of an unwanted litter of lab mixes.  She is three and a half years old and full of energy and love. Since coming into our rescue, she has done nothing but try to please everyone she comes in contact with. Even though she had a rough start in life she holds out "hope" that her day will come and she will become part of a permanent home.  Hope loves to go on walks, have belly rubs and play in the water.  She is looking for her special family.  Hope has been spayed, up to date on all shots, and is on heart worm preventative.  All she needs now is human to call her own! 

Adoption Fee:$200
Transport Fee: $160

COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! IF you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

Please email for an Application or copy and paste the following URL:

https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

Upon receipt of your application, the rescuer and foster in AL will contact you so you can ask any specific questions you may have!

If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement! Thank you for your understanding and consideration and for helping the dogs and puppies in need!

Adoption Donation: Unless otherwise stated in the pet's bio, our standard adoption fee is $350 which covers age appropriate vaccines (2 DHPP vax) and (Rabies vax if 12 weeks and older), utd on flea/tick prevention and heartworm prevention, spay or neuter of pet, bi-weekly worming, heartworm test @ age 6 months or older, microchip, fostering costs and health certificate.

We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Hope has been around several other dogs and a cat at her foster home.  She has done very well interacting with them.

BooBoo just participated in our rehabilitation program and is now looking for his very own home to help him practice all the lessons he learned! BooBoo is good with other dogs and knows basic manners around the home. He is currently in a foster home with children and acts appropriately, although we always recommend working with children and the dogs to ensure healthy boundaries and proper behavior from everyone. 

Boo is a very quiet puppy who just likes to be near his people. His ideal family will be willing to learn more about his rehabilitation process so that they can provide a smooth transition. He will do best in a home with calm, confident leadership, which AHAS is happy to help teach his adopters all about. 

Boo is neutered, up to date on vaccines, and heartworm negative. We require an adoption application, home visit, and adoption fee. animal.description:
Trilogy is special pup that came into the rescue from the Rescue's Veterinary Office.  The local shelter had found him wandering around town with a chain wrapped around his neck and front leg.  Unfortunately, this chain had been wrapped around him for sometime and had severely damaged the radial nerve in his front leg and he was left dragging the leg and was unusable.  After his leg was amputated, he ran around like he had been freed.  This amputation does not slow or hinder him at all, he is able to play, run, hike, climb stairs and do everything a 4 legged pup can do and he should not have any further issues with the amputated leg area.  

Trilogy was heartworm positive when he came to us, and was fully treated and is now on heartworm preventative.  He is also current on all vaccines, tested negative for any tick borne diseases, neutered and microchipped.  

If you are interested in Trilogy, his adoption fee is lowered due to his special needs,  He does need a family without other animals, and older children would be better.  He is a loyal, sweet pup that just wants to be loved on all day long!

animal.description:
Aries - Dutch Shepherd Mix - Male - 4 Years - www.twyla.org

If you'd like to know more about this dog please visit our website at www.Twyla.org

Meet Aries: This gorgeous young male Dutch Shepherd/Akita mix has the best ears! Aries is sweet and affectionate, also active and playful - he LOVES to run! Aries gets on well with other dogs, although he can be a bit bossy with them, so a good match is important. He is house and crate trained, walk ok on leash - that could use some polishing - and rides well in the car. He is not destructive in the house and is rather quiet, but he needs a good amount of exercise to satisfy is need to run, so he is looking for an active family that will take him running or biking and stimulates his brain with training and games. He does not like to be alone and is looking for an active home where someone is home a lot AND can give him the exercise he needs. He does need a well-maintained fence as he will exploit weaknesses or doors/gates left not quite shut.

Being a Shepherd mix, he does shed and needs regular brushing but he is well worth the effort as he is a head-turner wherever he goes!

***Please note: All dogs are fostered in private homes of volunteers, so to meet a dog please fill out an Adoption Application on our website (http://www.twyla.org/adopt/our-adoption-process) so we may setup a private meetup with the dog or coordinate for an Introduction at the next general Adoption Meet  and Greet (as listed on our website: (http://www.twyla.org/upcoming-events), as not all dogs attend all Meet and Greets***

animal.description:
* Adoptable status on-hold pending behavior modification training. **

We are so proud of this amazing dog! Izzi (aka: Isabella) is full of zest for life. Born April 2018; 33 pounds.

Izzi was found dumped on a country road as a puppy and taken to a municipal rural shelter where we rescued her. She is a super survivor with a strong will to spread joy wherever she goes. (Izzi's momma was also rescued and she was a Bull Terrier/cattledog and we think Izzi also has smooth fox terrier in her.)

Izzi is very smart! She knows all basic obedience, has great leash manners and is a high-energy gal. Izzi learns a lot from other dogs in her foster home and does best with large male dogs.

Izzi's a very talented runner and jumper; she seems to want to fly -- and really enjoys playing fetch with a ball or soft frisbee. The best forever home for Izzi will offer an active lifestyle. Izzi has a very curious nature and really enjoys all the adventure found playing in a secure yard. Physical and mental exercise makes Izzi a happy dog! She likes to watch birds sing and cuddle with her person.

Izzi is too interested in little things that run -- so for that reason, a home without children or small animals is required for this darling of a dog.

Izzi is spayed, current on vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. Izzi's adoption contribution is $150. Contact SacredPawsDogs@gmail.com to learn more about beautiful Izzi!

animal.description:
Hi … my name is Mango Grace and here are some things you need to know about me:

Mango Grace is a really sweet girl … once she trusts you.  She is a girl who requires a little extra patience and some special handling, but she is SOOOO worth the investment of time and love.

Mango was a stray who ‘picked’ a family that she found. All the people in the family loved her, but Mango’s high energy and exuberance proved to be too much for their older dogs.  Her play style with other dogs is rough-tumble and in-your-face, and not all other dogs are OK with that.  Once she trusts you, she is a velcro dog with her people. She does well with some of her foster friends, but will always need more socialization and she may never be a  'go everywhere' dog. Mango will thrive with a new family with people who have time to spend with her, who are willing to get training for her, who are willing to make sure she gets plenty of exercise … who are willing to love her and work with her to become the best dog she can be. Could that be you?

Please read the rest of Mango Grace's bio below to learn more about her!

If you think Mango might be the perfect pup for you, please go to www.allamericanmuttrescue.org, click on Forms/Application and complete your adoption application online.

Approximate age/birthdate:  born ~ April 2015

 Weight/size: 45-50 lbs

 Housebroken:  YES (if you do your part letting her out regularly)

 Crate trained:  YES

 Personality:  busy, wary of new people at first, playful

Energy level:  very energetic, rough and tumble play style
 
Fenced yard required?:   YES ... No Exceptions.  Mango would be a danger to neighborhood cats and possibly small dogs. She has a high prey drive and is a bit 'dog selective'

Does he/she jump fences?  NO (but she could if she wanted to)

Leash walk:  YES … high energy so will still pull

 Obedience training:  Knows ‘sit’

Riding in vehicles:  RIDES OK … gets a little stressed at first          

 Spayed/neutered:   YES

 Up-to-date on routine vaccinations:   YES

 Microchipped:  NO but a chip will be provided

 Social with other dogs:  YES but she is selective about her friends and not all other dogs are tolerant of her unfiltered energy.  Slow, proper introductions to any new dogs is a MUST with her.  She does not do well with smaller dogs.

Social with cats: NO CATS … she plays far too rough and has a high prey drive

Good with children:  Her energy may be overwhelming for small children.  Will be better with children 12 years old and up

Adoption donation: $175

We are an all-volunteer group, so please be patient and understand that it takes an average of 7-14 days to process the applications including reference checks, follow-up questions and home visits.  You can expedite the process by providing accurate email addresses for all your references.  Time to make phone calls is limited and we often have multiple applications in process.  We make every effort to move through them as quickly as possible.

When your application is approved, we will schedule a meet-and-greet to see if Mango picks you too. 

If it seems that the adoption will be a good match for all, there is an adoption fee, and an adoption contract to be signed. 
Please feel free to email weluvpups@hotmail.com if you have additional questions.
animal.name: Mango Grace

If you find a dog you want to meet in person, please go to www.secondchancedogrescue.org and complete an application. We will make every attempt to process all applications within 3 business days of receipt.

// //

Single curmudgeon canine male with managed medical issue is seeking a single caring human female of means for companionship and to assist with simple daily canine care. If you are still reading this then please read on about me!

Meet Macaroni, or Mac for short. Mac is a loving and loyal nine year old, 14 pound Chihuaha. He is a little bit shy at first but in his foster's home Mac has blossomed into a relaxed and loving companion. Mac will pick one person to be "his person", and really does prefer women. Macaroni walks well on a leash, is crate trained, and is doing very well with his house training and will use pee pads. He appreciates having a comfy safe spot of his very own to retreat for reflection and a good nap. At night, he is expert at burrowing under the covers to sleep at your feet. Mac is good with other friendly dogs, and respectful of the foster's dog-tolerant cat. He would do best in a female household without small children or lots of visitors. Mac travels in a car okay, but he would not be a good long-distance or airplane traveler.

Macaroni loves a good cuddle on the couch, knows how to be a good companion without going over the top, and would be a good friend for life! Macaroni is neutered, microchipped and current on his vaccines. Mac is on medications to prevent seizures which is required three times daily according to schedule. His adoption fee is $200.

All Second Chance Dog Rescue dogs are spayed/neutered, are up to date on vaccines and have microchips prior to adoption.

Adoption fees vary depending on age of dog. Fees help Second Chance Dog Rescue cover spay/neuter costs,

vaccinations, medical treatments,

food and supplies. Please go to

www.secondchancedogrescue.org

and complete an application today!

All dogs live in private foster homes until they are adopted.

Hi … my name is Joy and here are some things you need to know about me:

Can you believe I was in 'doggy jail'?  I think I had a family once, but no one came to find me.  Foster Mom says 'It's their loss' ... whatever that means.  I try to be a very good girl, and most of the time I do OK, but sometimes I get really rowdy when I have other rowdy friends to play with.  And cats just bring out the worst in me.  Sorry.  Do you have room in your family for me?

This sweet girl is so much fun to be around.  She’s playful, sweet, snuggly, loveable … and some days she even listens well.  She’s a very smart girl and learns quickly.  She has a little shar-pei stubborn streak but she really does care whether her people are happy or not ... until she sees a cat ... or a squirrel ... or a deer ... anything that feels she must chase and eliminate.  She’s good with her foster siblings … especially loves playing with a puppy that looks like her little doppleganger!  She’s pretty even-tempered but she could definitely hold her ground if somebody else started something.  An experienced dog person and some obedience classes will do wonders to polish up this diamond-in-the-ruff!

Approximate age/birthdate:  born ~2014

Weight/size: 45 lbs

 Housebroken:  YES

 Crate trained:  YES … but she HATES being crated and will be very vocal about it

 Personality: happy, sweet, loving, playful

Energy level:  medium/high … she’s part lab so she’s a perpetual puppy

Fenced yard required?:   YES (no exceptions) … she needs a place to safely run and play off-leash to work off energy and she has a very high prey drive.  She will run off chasing deer, rabbits, squirrels ... the neighbor's cats ... etc.  

Does he/she jump fences?  NO

Leash walk:  YES

Obedience training:  Knows ‘sit’ … she’s very smart and learns new things quickly

 Riding in vehicles:  RIDES OK      

 Spayed/neutered:   YES

 Up-to-date on routine vaccinations:   YES

 Microchipped:   YES

 Social with other dogs:  YES 

 Social with cats:  NO CATS ... she has a high prey drive and will do harm to cats

Good with children:  Children over 10.  Her size and energy might prove to be too much for younger children.

Adoption donation:  $175

If you think Joy might be the perfect pup for you, please go to www.allamericanmuttrescue.org, click on Forms/Application and complete your adoption application online.

animal.description:
Meet Bo Dewey – It's been a whole YEAR since this boy was adopted and unfortunately he is being returned to rescue due to a divorce. . He’s approx. 4 years old, up to date on all vaccines and neutered.
 
Bo is a big, goofy, cuddly boy who loves to play and make everyone laugh. He was very appropriate with his human foster sisters and takes great correction from their female dog while he was in foster. 
 
Bo is house trained and crate trained. A home with a fenced in yard and experience with large dogs is preferred as he’s a BIG, strong boy. Bo does not do well with cats or animals smaller than him, they confuse him. He will also need his training to be kept up on, which is going great! He's learning to focus and not be so excitable all the time. If anyone is interested, we have videos of Bo playing the foster’s children. He loves being outside, whether it's a baby pool or running in the snow

If you are interested in adopting this big boy - please submit your application today! 
https://queencitypitties.com/adoption-application/

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hopper is now almost 5 years old and remains in a foster home where she is very comfortable and settled. Hopper remains 'Hopperish' - she has bursts of extreme energy which consists of jumping and pawing, followed by typical greyhound settled behavior. Hopper continues to love stuffies and her food, and is clean in the house. Hopper is sometimes wary of people and can be growly towards the other dogs in her foster home. Original PostingM's Free Hopper is a very pretty little girl. She is friendly and playful when she feels comfortable and secure. She likes to snuggle and to bury her head into your lap or legs. She walks very nicely on leash. Hopper likes people and other dogs. This 2 year old is a sibling to Free Business 'Billy' and Free Dara. She turned 2 in August and is cat tolerant with supervision.Foster Update 6/26/2017
Hopper will be 4 years old in August, 2017 and is currently in a foster home. She is a unique greyhound girl who is active and interactive. She loves her stuffy toys, is a good eater and is housebroken. Hopper is often very enthusiastic and would do best in a home without small children. Hopper at times can be growly with the other dogs, so close supervision is required. She requires a calm, authoritative owner who can deal with Hopper at her best (and sometimes worst).
Original Foster Update: Free Hopper is looking out for her forever home. She is not only beautiful but so very sweet. She is very well behaved and gets along with my 4 cats and her small dog friends. She loves belly rubs and has the most adorable little hop when excited. She also smiles when happy.
Inmate Handler Update 1/13/2016:'Hopper is a very interesting girl. She is loving and thinks that she is a princess and can also sometimes be a little bossy. Her personality is one of a kind. Not only that but her coat has a very black sheen to it that gleams when in the light. A coat that is also very soft and a delicate frame. Hopper is great on the leash and does not use the bathroom indoors and loves to play.'M's Free Hopper is back with GFNJ as it was just not a good match. She is in a foster home and doing just great. She's young and learns quickly. She ignores the cats in the foster home, has easily mastered the stairs, crates easily, has no space issues and corrects very easily with a firm 'Hey'.This young 2 year old is looking for her forever home.

animal.description:
Say Hello to Gunner!

Gunner is a 1.5yr old English Bulldog and weighs about 40lbs. He has a condition called Spina Bifida and it will require him to wear diapers for the rest of his life. However, it doesn't keep him from being a regular dog who enjoys walks and play time with his people. He also does well with older children. When not playing, his favorite place to be is right next to you on the sofa for snuggles. He is such a cuddle bug! And who can resist that face?

Gunner wants all of the attention and lovin' for himself and needs to be an only dog. He is currently being fostered with our trainer in Denver. But he would love a home of his very own where he can watch movies on the sofa and run around in the backyard. 

His adoption includes the following training:  3 in home sessions (the first being when he is brought to his forever home). 2 six week classes (basic obedience & intermediate obedience) and unlimited play groups for 3 month.

See more Gunner pics on facebook at https://www.facebook.com/moemoesrescue/photos/pcb.853437715041129/853437175041183/?type=3&theater

Apply to adopt Gunner at http://www.moemoesrescue.com/

animal.description:
Rocky, a Lab/Staffie mix born July 2016, is looking for a new home with people who will love and understand him. Although he has had a rough start to life, with the right training and positive reinforcement, this boy will be a faithful companion. He will come with training so we can be sure he will live a great life and you will be equipped to deal with and learn all about how to help him gain confidence. In his previous home, Rocky was severely abused and ended up in the shelter. That environment was not conducive to helping him heal so we worked together to get him into a loving home where he could learn all about people and learn to trust them. He will need the proper introduction with all resident dogs and children over the age of 12 to ensure a great long-term relationship. Young children prove to be too unpredictable for Rocky, so we are recommending no children or children over the age of 12. Rocky has so much potential to be the most loving companion with the right family. He will thrive most in a home with a fenced in yard so he can have space when he needs it and a family that is experienced with dogs.

Rocky needs time to feel safe with new people. Interested adopters should expect a few meetings for Rocky to get to know them. A trainer will be a part of the process to help Rocky and his new owners work well together.

Update from foster 12/26/18: Rocky is a big sweetheart that shows his best self in environments where he feels safe and relaxed. Having struggled with fear and anxiety around strangers and loud noises, Rocky has come a long way and enjoys going on outings and doesnt mind the vacuum as much anymore. He knows sit, shake and lie down and comes when hes called. He is well house-trained and does well in a crate. He loves his squeaky toys and enjoys a good game of fetch with them. Rocky may need some time to warm up to you, your kids or other dogs. If those around him are calm and patient, he will more likely feel safe. When that happens, he will be your biggest fan.

Before applying to adopt Rocky, you need to be familiar with your local breed-specific legislation regarding Pit Bulls. Applicants must live within 50 miles of the Omaha/Council Bluffs area.

The suggested adoption donation for Rocky is $350, which is TAX DEDUCTIBLE, and goes toward providing supportive services to animals inthe home, as well as the high cost of vetting our dogs in rescue. If you would like to welcome Rocky into your home, please begin by submitting our AdoptionApplication. The adoptions for all of our dogs will take place in the Omaha,
NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver the dogs.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

If you would like to learn more about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue, or donate to our dogs, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com. We invite you to visit our Facebook Page, and when you visit, please don't forget to Like our Facebook page so that you wont miss any information about our dogs and events!

animal.description:
SPONSORED - ADOPTION FEE WAIVED! Oh my! We have a beauty for you with gray and gorgeous Gemma! Our gal has waited a long time to find you. We rescued Gemma with her newly born litter of puppies after they ended up in a high intake shelter. Of course, Gemma was a wonderful mom and now that all of her puppies have been adopted, she's dreaming of a forever home for herself! Large at 83 pounds, Gemma is sturdy and has lots to love on.  With all Gemma has been through, she is a little nervous upon introductions, but the more she trusts, her sweetness begins to blossom.  When we first rescued Gemma, she was afraid to be outside, but now she enjoys being outside and rolling around in the grass. Gemma needs someone with lots of love to give and patience.  Gemma is crate trained. Gemma is a laid back gal and friendly. Her lazy personality will have you finding her snoozing close to you. She does need to be in a home without cats. Gemma is just waiting to browse through adoption applications at ITVRescue.org. Gemma has a guardian angel who sponsored her adoption fee so her adoption fee is waived! Gemma is just a big love bug who needs an easy going home to live out the leisurely life she so deserves! She can't wait to become part of your family and be homeless no more! See video of Gemma at https://www.facebook.com/courtney.kniese/videos/2119146291438567/

All of our animals are examined by a veterinarian, given age-appropriate vaccinations, dewormed, microchipped, spayed or neutered, heartworm tested and treated if necessary.

Please realize that many of our animals are kept in foster homes. Please complete an adoption application at http://itvrescue.org/adoption-application/ in order to meet with one of our animals. There is no obligation in completing the application, but it helps us find an animal that is most appropriate for your family.  The ITV Rescue Center is open Tuesdays 12-5; Wednesdays 12-7; Thursdays 12-5; Fridays 12-5 and Saturdays 10-5.  The Rescue Center is located at 1417 N. Stockwell Road.  You are welcome to come to our rescue center during open hours to see all of our great adoptable animals. Thank you for your interest in our animals!

NOTE: Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

animal.description:
MEET LAYLA 4!! **Please Note: This is a courtesy post for another rescue; different adoption fees/policy apply.

Meet Layla! Layla was adopted from a high kill shelter on May 5th 2018. Her adopter was looking for a companion dog for her dog, and it seemed like a great fit. Unfortunately when they got home Layla showed some severe resource guarding issues. Her adopter worked with her for months, and has got it about 80% under control. However there are still some random acts of aggression between Layla and the adopters dog, which results In Layla being kenneled while her owner is gone to work, which isn't fair to such a sweet dog. Layla is super sweet with people doesn't have a mean bone in her body towards humans, and you can truly tell all she wants is love and affection. Layla has most likely had a rough past. She was adopted and returned to the shelter 3 times, which is why her current owner will not just dump her back there. She is looking for the perfect home for this well deserving dog.

We believe Layla is about 3 - 5yrs old. She is spayed, house trained, doggy door efficient, and kennel trained. She is very calm and mellow. Loves water, and loves to snuggle humans. She smiles when she petted or given attention, she loves treats and chew toys and bones. She is the perfect low maintenance companion. She has come such a long way since she escaped the shelter for the last time, and she is looking for her perfect forever home. I cannot stress enough how amazing sweet this pup is. Guaranteed to melt your heart with her loving cuddles. , , Layla is dog tolerant, but wouldn't be able to be left unsupervised with other dogs. She loves puppies she has some motherly instincts, so she may have been a mom before. She is good with older kids and maybe younger, given the proper introduction. She may do okay with a cat given the right introduction, but has never been around them. Come meet her today and see if shes the right fit for your family.

For more information or to meet this pet, please complete an application or send email to info@underdogaz.com

If you're reading this via a pet-search site, please view this pet's page

at www.UnderdogAZ.com/animals

for more photos and details.

*As far away as Barrie and Cambridge, Ontario & as far away as the Gatineau, Quebec area*
**NO Exceptions**

BHRR's Burst - Female - Black Lab/Great DaneX - ~4 years of age, utd on vaccines, microchipped, good with other dogs & good with people, unknown with cats(integration is key!) has had some obedience(this does not exclude our mandatory adoption clause of a full round of obedience being required - NO EXCEPTIONS!)

NOTE: All blogs(scroll to the very bottom and then read upwards) and our PetFinder animal lists are kept utd so yes, BHRR's Burst is still available. 

Please do not EMAIL asking such and, please do go to her blog to read about her before contacting us. Almost all of your questions will be answered in her very detailed blog. READ the blog from the bottom up once on the blog. 

Please familiarize yourself with BHRR's adoption mandates, processes plus policies before contacting us about a BHRR animal. 

Our PetFinder and our www.birchhaven.org websites will answer most of your questions. Therefore,do not contact us asking us what our policies are,or what our adoption area is or what her adoption fee is. BHRR is a federally registered NPO operated solely by Volunteers. We are NOT a shelter or a pound. 

You cannot just drop by to visit her. She resides in a loving home, not a kennel.

When contacting BHRR; please send a short introduction re: your home etc. Inquires that only ask a one liner re: adoption fees shall not be returned. The adoption cost(from a r/q Rescue) or purchase cost(if you purchase from a reputable/quality Breeder is the LEAST that you shall pay over the lifetime of proper care of your pet).

animal.description:
Name : Snuggles
Age:  1/11/2011
Sex:   Female
Size:  12 pounds

Location : Chicago IL, south suburban area

Adoption Fee: $400.00
Adoptions available for this dog must be Local Only.
Local adoptions considered within 50 miles of zip code 60451

Health: arthritis in spine and knee luxation
              Dry eye.

Temperament: Extremely Shy & Timid

My Ideal Home: quiet (no children) with a fenced yard

**We would love to talk to you about Snuggles or any of our other available dogs but we first need everyone to go to our website and submit an adoption application. All Inquiries Require an Adoption Application to be Submitted  

Meet Snuggles,
Rescued by the Police from an unfit home situation and turned over to JCCARE. Snuggles is learning to be loved and pampered in a home.
Snuggles is shy and timid. Her name is misleading as she does not like to be snuggled.
 She is unsure of everyday things most dogs don’t even notice.
She is afraid of loud noise, quick movements and sometimes hesitates to go through an open door. Her foster family has to find her and try to pick her up (sometimes she runs & hides) to go outside often.
She has learned how to use potty pads but still hesitates to go outside.
She is still learning to trust & enjoy the humans in his foster home, Sometimes wagging her tail and sometimes hiding.
 
Her future:
A quiet family that will allow Snuggles to be loved on her terms. 
At this point Snuggles does not really enjoy sitting and cuddling on a lap but does enjoy being pet if not held. (sometimes) Things may change as she adjusts to home life but for now 
Snuggles will need the following:
A home on the quiet side.
A home with adults only.
A home with a secure fenced yard as Snuggles does not walk on leash and is terrified of the leash.
A home with another well manured, well-adjusted, small dog to help her overcome her emotional anxiety.
A home that is financially secure to care for her medical needs.

**Due to her arthritis in her back she should not jump down from furniture or be expected to take long walks / runs. This is a lifelong condition that will require anti-inflammatory/pain medication during "flare ups", Flares can be triggered for no obvious reason or due to weather or activity.
** Due to her dry eyes snuggles will require daily prescription medication for the rest of her life. This will require veterinarian  prescription eye drops administered in both eyes 2-3 times a day. 

Would you like to give sweet Snug Bug a forever home? 
Please fill out the adoption application from our website and someone will contact you with more information about Snuggles.

LOCAL ADOPTION ONLY. ( no further than 50 miles from 60451)


WWW.Japanesechinrescue.org

Adoption Process: To adopt a Chin from JCCARE, start by filling out the application found on our website at www.japanesechinrescue.org. The application is under the Forms menu.

If you aren’t ready to adopt yet but would like to help this dog, please click on the purple SPONSOR ME button above the name.   Your donation will help us to pay for the care of this dog until he/she finds a furever home.

JCCARE also maintains the lives of many senior and special needs Chin in our “Sanctuary” program.  These dogs are not listed on petfinder, as their health issues make them unlikely to ever be adopted.   If you are a lover of the breed, could you please consider sponsoring one of our seniors?   You can find their pictures and stories under OUR CHIN on our web site: www.japanesechinrescue.org

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullBreed: Pit Bull Terrier Gender: Male Estimated Date of Birth: January 12, 2017 Size: 53 lbs Location: Dallas, GA
RESCUING DECKER
One of the shelter workers at Dekalb sent out a plea for Decker. She had a soft-spot for his sweet nature and desperation for affection. Decker was at the shelter for 2 weeks with clear neurological issues causing his balance to be off and he tumbled over constantly. He was in need of vet care and we were able to get him what he needs.
ABOUT DECKER
Although Decker cannot walk very far without falling over, he is super sweet and dog friendly. He saw Dr Parks at GVS and his issues are definitely cerebral. A blood test revealed Decker has Cerebellar Ataxia (NCL-A) which is an autosomal recessive neurological disease. His balance and vision will progressively get worse. Decker has to be supported 100% by a person in order to walk. He has a full body harness to make it a little bit easier, but when he's indoors, he is happy to sit on the couch with you. When he is supported by his harness and his person, he loves being outside and loves to 'chase' squirrels (we just walking him where he wants to go and let him pretend). His crate needs to be padded because of his involuntary jerking motions that cause him to sway from side to side and fall over into the crate walls. He is crate-trained, but does not have access to roam freely in the house at this time. He is currently located at the Pit Bull Palace where there is not a space customized to suit his needs to prevent him from injuring himself. Decker needs time to warm up to new people and is not suited for a home with kids. He truly relies 100% on people and would love a foster or adopter that is willing and able to accommodate his special needs.
Our adoption fee is $300. All dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed or neutered, micro-chipped, on heartworm prevention, and are fed top of the line grain-free food.www.savingpitbulls.org

animal.description:
Hi!  My name is Bernie.  I'm an adult pointer labrador retriever  mix male about 5 years old who ended up in the very high kill shelter in San Bernardino City.  Luckily for me, Rescue came and got me out of there before I ran into trouble.  Whew!  Not a fun place.  I was lucky to go into foster care but my foster dad moved and now I'm back at the kennel.  I am good with pretty much all dogs, altho perhaps not with tiny dogs, since I have retained the pointer hunting traints .I am a well behaved boy .. know my house manners, ride nicely in the car (I do love to stick my head out the window), and walk reasonably well on leash.  I love to hunt lizards so some property i would have space to hunt lizards would be great.   I am a very social boy and  I would not like living alone and not having my family or friends around.  I'm a strong dog consistent with my lab genes and would be best with an experienced dog owner.   I would be great with an active family who hikes bikes jogs or runs or is involved in other outdoor activities where a friendly big dog can join in.  I am neutered (I came into the shelter that way) and vaccinated.  I would so love to have my own family to love .. could it be yours?

If you are interested in me, please contact Dalmatian Rescue of Southern California, Inc. by emailat dalrescue@sbcglobal.net. and ask about me.    To ensure I would be a good fit with your family, Rescue requires the completion of an adoption questionnaire, but once approved, arrangements can be quickly made for you and your family to come meet me and my friends at the kennel where I live.  I love meeting new folks so please contact Dalmatian Rescue and ask about me as soon as you can.

To learn more about Dalmatian Rescue of Southern California, Inc., a 501c3 non-profit charity, and to see all of our available dogs, please visit our website at www.dalrescuesocal.com.  You can also visit us on our facebook page at www.facebook.com/spottyfriends.  We love seeing your photos and posts about life with your spotty friends so please keep them coming.  Thanks!

animal.description:
Lily is a beautiful labrador mix - young and healthy with a fun loving spirit.  She loves life and it shows!!  

Lily was dumped by a church with all her belongings and a good samaritan found her and brought her to us.  It was apparent when Lily came to us that the previous owner had done nothing to help Lily be a good dog.  She had no manners whatsoever...so much energy and no idea how to use it.  

In the short month Lily has been with us, she has crate trained herself, learned sit and down like a pro, is loose leash walking, learned to play fetch, and discovered the joys of a puppy pool.  

This young girl is gorgeous, smart and wants nothing more than to please you.  Lily will need an active household and someone who will continue working with her on basic obedience and will help her find jobs to keep her little mind and body busy. 

Lilly will need an experienced dog owner, one that is confident, consistent, and can give her the guidance she needs to grow into the best dog she can be.

If interested in Lily, head to our website (http://lifelongfriends.org/adoptions) and fill out an adoption application!

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: Lily enjoys the company of adults and children,  but prefers to be an only pet. She is to always be on a leash when outside the house or fenced yard. She is housebroken and loves to swim. She is not to be around other pets.

animal.description:
Hey there nice hooman, whats your sign? Im too awesome to have just one so they call me Zodiac. Im a 2 year old female Dutch Shepherd mix and Im completely star-struck by you and ready to join your pack. I am easy going and loving like a Gemini so you and I can cuddle on the couch on those cold evenings. Im well-disciplined and dependable like Capricorn so you dont have to worry about me destroying the house and yes, I am house-trained. Im fun and adventurous like Leo so lets take car trips as often as we can, I love the car and will behave inside it. Im brave and confident like Aries so I will protect you from the things I dont get along with namely small dogs and cats, but I would be best suited as an only dog. Im can be a little stubborn like the bull Taurus so lets make a date night out of some obedience training, I need help on the leash. You may not know this, but the Zodiac was originally created as a system to measure time and its about time for me to find the furever home with the six-foot fence Ive been dreaming of. If you can give me that then Ill give you all the love in the heavens. 

*BSL Restrictions apply, must own home & cannot live in a breed restricted area.

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Hi, i’m Manning!  I’ve been at Missy’s Haven for about 18 months now but I don’t complain.  See I’m not very fond of others, they make me nervous.  I love my foster mommy, she gives me kisses, belly rubs, treats every day, and even hangs out with us and watches tv.  

If you want to come read to me, see if we may be a match let the wonderful people at MHCR know.  If not it’s okay, like I said they take great care of me and I even have a bunch of new friends.  

I’ve We don’t get the chance to meet, You can help by sponsoring me and all us old timers here, Monetary donations are nice but they always need used or gently used towels, rub a dub dub!  Paper towels, bleach, I love Science Diet small bites, and oh yea, those soft doggy treats.  

- - Manning - - 

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application, once submitted we will contact you for a meeting.  Also, we only adopt young puppies out of area once they reach 10 weeks old.  OUT OF STATE ADOPTIONS: We do allow out-of-state adoptions for dogs, however, the adopter MUST pay for all transportation fees.  NOTE: As we believe proper healthcare of one's pet is a requirement of good ownership, MHCR only adopts out dogs that have been fully vetted and altered. ADOPTION FEE: (includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, medicines and medical procedures, if necessary) Please LIKE and share our Facebook page www.facebook.com/missyshavencr Thanks!

Please apply http://www.missyshavencr.org if you are interested in adopting from Missy’s Haven Canine Rescue. More information available by contacting info@missyshavencr.org

animal.description:
Brigitta is a 8 year old German Shepherd. She is a sweet and loving dog that loves to go for walks, play frisbee, and lounge in her pool. She's very smart and knows basic commands such as sit, down, wait, shake, and touch. She does have anxiety and would benefit from a calm environment with no children or pets. She has paperwork from the breeder, vet records, and she is microchipped. Brigitta has recently started to show some pain in her hips which could possibly be arthritis. She is currently on a joint supplement which seems to help. Brigitta's perfect home will be with a person who will respect her boundaries. It should be a low-traffic, quiet home with no children, no other pets, and few visitors.

The suggested adoption donation for Brigitta is $150, which is TAX DEDUCTIBLE, and goes toward providing supportive services to animals in the home, as well as the high cost of vetting our dogs in rescue. If you would like to welcome Brigitta into your home, please begin by submitting our Adoption Application. The adoptions for all of our dogs will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver the dogs. If you would like to learn more about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue, or donate to our dogs, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com. We invite you to visit our Facebook Page, and when you visit, please don't forget to Like our Facebook page so that you wont miss any information about our dogs and events!

animal.description:
Introducing gorgeous 9 years young Chloe, a Rhodesian Ridgeback mix. Classic coloring, eyes that look into your heart, and a megawatt smile,

 Chloe is ready to find her happily ever after. 

Chloe's perfect day consists of easy walks, some playtime, and lots of cuddle time with her person. She's the perfect TV buddy! 

Chloe does not like to share her things, so an experienced person who understands when to leave her alone is needed. She will warn you, but what's hers is hers.

 Chloe knows 'sit' and 'high five', and happily shows off her skills in exchange for a treat which she gently takes. 

Chloe loves children (older children suggested), gets along with cats, and can be dog selective.

 Our superstar is housetrained, crate trained, and looking for a person to provide structure, routine, and guidance to be the best she can be. She's such a love, and is move-in ready, 

up to date with vaccinations, spayed, and microchipped.
Let's get her home!
